          h2 We present a low-cost wireless stethoscope with an artificial intelligence (AI) back-end to help both semi-trained and expert medical professionals to diagnose cardiac abnormalities 
          p The coronavirus pandemic has created a deleterious impact throughout the world. Developing countries are particularly hard-hit, as they scramble to use limited resources, both financial and personnel, to battle its growing spread. Novel cost effective medical devices which cater to the unique needs of this hour are therefore of utmost importance. Here we present a low-cost wireless stethoscope with an artificial intelligence (AI) back-end to help both semi-trained and expert medical professionals to diagnose cardiac abnormalities while wearing personal protective equipment or maintaining a safe distance from the patient. Cardiac complications are implicated in a significant portion of coronavirus patients, and patients with underlying cardiac diseases are known to be at a higher risk of mortality.  However, existing wireless stethoscopes with AI-support are either simply unaffordable or unavailable in many developing countries touting large populations (e.g. India, Brazil). Therefore, our stethoscope: the <b>Intelliscope</b>, can become a game-changer helping tackle this pandemic in such resource-constrained environments.
